{{Infobox person | name = David Miles Huber | image = | caption = David Miles Huber | birth_name= David Miles Huber | known_for = American composer and Record Producer | occupation = composer and producer }}
'''David Miles Huber''' is an American [[composer]] and [[Record producer|producer]] in the [[downtempo]], [[Ambient music|ambient]] and [[Dance music|dance]] genres. He is also the author of numerous books on [[Sound recording and reproduction|recording]] and [[electronic music]]. Huber's CD series ''Relaxation and Meditation with Music and Nature'' has sold over one million copies. His latest music and collaborations are available through the 51bpm [[independent record label]]. Huber's most prominent book; ''Modern Recording Techniques'' was sold over 250,000 copies and became a standard recording industry text.
Huber received his degree in music technology from [[Indiana University]] (I.M.P.), and was the first American to be admitted into the [[Tonmeister]] program at the [[University of Surrey]] in [[Guildford]], [[Surrey]], [[England]].<ref>{{cite web|title=David Miles Huber|last=Huber|first=David|url=http://davidmileshuber.com/}}</ref>
==Selected discography== *''Colabs'' (2008), 51bm.com llc - 51bpm-005CD (stereo CD) - one CD<ref name=discography1>{{cite web|last=Huber|first=David|title=Colabs|url=http://davidmileshuber.com/|accessdate=5 April 2013}}</ref>{{primary source inline|date=January 2017}} *''Colabs'' (2008), 51bm.com llc - 51bpm-008dtsCD (surround dts CD) - one surround dts CD<ref name=discography2>{{cite web|last=Huber|first=David|title=Colabs 2008|url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees?category=186|accessdate=5 April 2013}}</ref> *''Relaxation and Meditation with Music and Nature'' (1993), Delta Music - two 5-CD sets<ref>{{cite web|last=Huber|first=David|title=Relaxation & Meditation With Music & Nature|url=http://davidmileshuber.com/|accessdate=5 April 2013}}</ref> *''Between the Sea & the Sky'' (1996), Delta Music - 5-CD box set<ref name="Huber">{{cite web|last=Huber|first=David|title=Between the Sea & The Sky|url=http://davidmileshuber.com/|accessdate=5 April 2013}}</ref> {{primary source inline|date=January 2017}} *''Roads'' (1979), 51bpm.com llc - 51bpm-001DL (stereo download)<ref name="Huber"/> {{primary source inline|date=January 2017}} *''Chamberland'' (2012), 51bm.com llc<ref name=discography1/>{{primary source inline|date=January 2017}} Nominated for Best Surround Sound Album (55th Annual Grammy Awards Winner 2013)<ref>{{cite web|last=Huber|first=David|title=55th Annual Grammy Awards|url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees/|accessdate=23 April 2013}}</ref>
==Selected bibliography== *''Audio Production Techniques for Video''. H.W. Sams, 1987.<ref>{{cite book|last=Huber|first=David Miles|title=Audio production techniques for video|year=1987|publisher=Focal Pr.|location=Boston.[Mass.]|isbn=978-0240801483}}</ref> *''Microphone Manual: Design and Application''. H.W. Sams, 1988.<ref>{{cite book|last=Huber|first=David Miles|title=Microphone manual : design and application|year=1988|publisher=H.W. Sams|location=Indianapolis, Ind., USA|isbn=978-0672225987|edition=1st}}</ref> *''Random Access Audio''. SAMS Pub., 1992.<ref>{{cite book|last=Huber|first=David Miles|title=Random access audio|year=1992|publisher=SAMS Pub.|location=Carmel, Ind., USA|isbn=978-0672300868}}</ref> *''Hard Disk Recording for Musicians''. Music Sales Corp, 1995.<ref>{{cite book|last=Huber|first=David Miles|title=Hard disk recording for musicians|year=1995|publisher=Amsco Publications|location=New York|isbn=978-0825614330}}</ref> *''Professional Microphone Techniques'' (with Philip Williams). Thomson Course Technology, 1998.<ref>{{cite book|last=Huber|first=David Miles|title=Professional microphone techniques|year=1998|publisher=MixBooks|location=Emeryville, CA|isbn=978-0872886858|edition=2. printing.}}</ref> *''Modern Recording Techniques'' (with Robert E. Runstein). Seventh edition, [[Elsevier]], 2010.<ref>{{cite book|last=Runstein|first=David Miles Huber, Robert E.|title=Modern recording techniques|year=2010|publisher=Focal Press/Elsevier|location=Amsterdam|isbn=978-0240810690|edition=7th}}</ref> *''The MIDI Manual: A Practical Guide to MIDI in the Project Studio''. Third edition, Elsevier, 2007.<ref>{{cite book|last=Huber|first=David Miles|title=The MIDI manual : a practical guide to MIDI in the project studio|year=2007|publisher=Elsevier/Focal Press|location=Amsterdam|isbn=978-0240807980|edition=3rd}}</ref>
