==Synopsis== Childhood photos from Nurith Avivâs family album evoke memories and reflections which lead her to encounters with researches in neuroscience. The film, released on DVD by Epicentre Films,<ref>{{cite AV media|url=http://www.epicentrefilms.com/dvd-Poetique-du-cerveau-Nurith|people=Aviv, Nurith|title=PoÃ©tique du cerveau|location=Paris|publisher=Epicentre Films|language=French|accessdate=26 April 2018|format=DVD|oclc=949902028|date=26 April 2016|trans-title=Poetics of the Brain}}</ref> weaves associative links between Avivâs personal biographical stories and interviews she conducts with neuroscientists about their work. These scientists, including Prof. Dr. Laurent Cohen, Prof. Dr. Yadin Dudai, and Prof. Dr. Vittorio Gallese, discuss topics partly related to Avivâs previous films: memory, bilingualism, reading, mirror-neurons, smell, and traces of experience.
